      <h1 class='title'>Democratic Republic of Congo: British Embassy, Kinshasa</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='lords-written-statements-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HL Deb 02 February 2005 vol 669 cc11-2WS</cite>
      
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_11ws' title='Col. 11WS &mdash; HL Deb 02 February 2005 vol 669 c11WS' name='column_11ws' href='#column_11ws' rel='bookmark'>11WS</a>
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S5LV0669P0-04604'>
        <a name='S5LV0669P0_20050202_LWS_2'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/ms-elizabeth-symons' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S5LV0669P0_20050202_LWS_2' title='Link to this speech by Ms Elizabeth Symons' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/ms-elizabeth-symons" title="Ms Elizabeth Symons">The Minister of State, Foreign and Commonwealth Office (Baroness Symons of Vernham Dean)</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para" id="S5LV0669P0-04604">In light of the continuing instability in the Democratic Republic<a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_12ws' title='Col. 12WS &mdash; HL Deb 02 February 2005 vol 669 c12WS' name='column_12ws' href='#column_12ws' rel='bookmark'>12WS</a>
          of Congo (DRC) and the fragile security situation in Kinshasa, the Government have authorised the deployment of armed guards to our British Embassy in Kinshasa in order to safeguard embassy staff and ensure the mission can continue to operate.</p><p id="S5LV0669P0-04605">The Government take seriously their obligations to contribute to peace and security in the DRC. We have a development programme for the DRC worth &#x00A3;34 million for the financial year 2004&#x2013;05. Upgrading the security of our embassy will enable staff to continue to contribute to the peace process in the DRC. The DRC Government have been informed of our intention and are content with the arrangements we propose to protect our staff.</p><p id="S5LV0669P0-04606">A UN arms embargo targeting rebel groups operating in the east of the country has been in place on the DRC since 28 July 2003. An EU embargo has been in place on the country since 7 April 1993. We fully support these measures and have informed the UN DRC Sanctions Committee and EU partners of the deployment.</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
